{
  "bio": [
    "Johnelle Hunt and her husband Johnnie (d. 2006) founded trucking firm JB Hunt Transport Services in 1969.",
    "Eight years earlier, they sold their home and started a rice hull packaging company.",
    "The Arkansas-based trucking business went public in 1983 and is now one of the biggest transportation companies in the nation, with $14.8 billion in sales.",
    "Hunt, who stepped down as corporate secretary in 2008, remains the firm's largest individual shareholder, with a nearly 18% stake.",
    "She donated $5 million to the J.B. and Johnelle Hunt Family Ozark Highlands Center, which opened in Springdale, Arkansas in December 2020."
  ],
  "about": [
    "The daughter of a poultry business owner, Hunt studied to be a teacher at University of Central Arkansas before leaving to marry J.B.",
    "Hunt was a part of the 11 inaugural inductees to the Arkansas Women's Hall of Fame, which opened in 2015."
  ]
